comments: Where’s Optimus Prime?
description:
Hello from Mars!

Nasa’s science rover Perseverance has landed safely on the floor of a vast Martian crater after piercing the atmosphere at 19,000kmh.

The most advanced astrobiology laboratory ever sent to another world will be searching for traces of ancient microbial life on the Red Planet.

The robotic vehicle sailed through space for nearly 7 months, covering 472 million km.

Moments after touchdown, Perseverance beamed back its first black-and-white images from the Martian surface, one of them showing the rover’s shadow cast on the desolate, rocky landing site.

Link in bio @straits_times
📸: AFP
#NASA #NASAMars #Mars #MarsLanding #Space #Galaxy #Perseverance #RedPlanet #JezeroCrater #StraitsTimes

comments: So heartwarming to hear their story
description:
A friendship has been forged between visually-impaired pedestrians and 5 migrant workers at Caldecott MRT station’s worksite.

"The workers are always there at the same spot waiting for us. It's become a norm for them to approach us immediately when we exit the fare gate," said Mr Edwin Khoo, who added that he has started to build rapport with the guides. 

"Sometimes I feel like I don't need the help as I know the route, but meeting them is really about talking to them and enjoying their company."

Link in bio @straits_times
📸: Kua Chee Siong
#StraitsTimes

comments: Bless you both for your kind deeds
description:
During the Covid-19 circuit breaker last year, migrant workers were not allowed to leave their dormitories, not even to get food.

After learning about their predicament, Mrs Cherie Tseng and her husband Tseng Wun Hsiung rang up friends and relatives for donations, looked for catering firms, as well as Grab drivers to deliver food.

In 2 weeks, they raised more than $100,000 to provide over 10,000 meals to about 670 workers. The funds also went towards topping up SIM cards for 1,500 workers.

Full story in bio @straits_times
📸: Yong Li Xuan
#StraitsTimes #Singapore #MigrantWorkers #Covid19 #Coronavirus

Full story in bio @straits_times ⁣
📸: Timothy David⁣
#Covid19 #coronavirus #StraitsTimes⁣

comments: A true hero of Singapore!
description:
Dr Chen Yongsheng lived apart from his family for 2 months so that he could volunteer at dormitories in Singapore during the Covid-19 outbreak.
When the migrant worker dormitories became a coronavirus hot spot, Dr Chen knew that he had to rise to the occasion.
He was among the first batch of volunteers who helped to set up medical operations at Tuas View Dormitory.
To many, this may seem like the act of an unsung hero, but to Dr Chen, he was merely responding to his call of duty as a doctor.
Link in bio @straits_times
📸: Ng Teng Fong General Hospital
#medicalheroes #coronavirus #covid19 #StraitsTimes

Dr Chen Yongsheng lived apart from his family for 2 months so that he could volunteer at dormitories in Singapore during the Covid-19 outbreak.
When the migrant worker dormitories became a coronavirus hot spot, Dr Chen knew that he had to rise to the occasion.
He was among the first batch of volunteers who helped to set up medical operations at Tuas View Dormitory.
To many, this may seem like the act of an unsung hero, but to Dr Chen, he was merely responding to his call of duty as a doctor.
Link in bio @straits_times
📸: Ng Teng Fong General Hospital
#medicalheroes #coronavirus #covid19 #StraitsTimes

description:
If Westlite Toh Guan sounds familiar, that is likely because it was among the first dormitories to be gazetted as an isolation area during the Covid-19 pandemic.⁣
Today, it houses 195 workers who are healthy or have recovered from Covid-19, and they will be able to resume work soon.⁣
Full story bio @straits_times⁣
📸: Mark Cheong⁣
#StraitsTimes #Singapore #Covid19

If Westlite Toh Guan sounds familiar, that is likely because it was among the first dormitories to be gazetted as an isolation area during the Covid-19 pandemic.⁣
Today, it houses 195 workers who are healthy or have recovered from Covid-19, and they will be able to resume work soon.⁣
Full story bio @straits_times⁣
📸: Mark Cheong⁣
#StraitsTimes #Singapore #Covid19

description:
Meet Rajendran Raja, who works as a plumber for HDB blocks. ⁣
The 24-year-old from India, along with several other migrant workers, are now helping frontliners in the fight against Covid-19 in their dormitories. Their efforts include helping to record details of sick workers, distributing food and conducting briefings. ⁣
📸: Kua Chee Siong⁣
#Covid19 #coronavirus #StraitsTimes
